    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <h1>Jetalsar Town & Junction</h1>
            <p>A Critical Railway Hub of Saurashtra</p>
        </header>
        
        <p>
            **Jetalsar** is a small town in the Rajkot district of Gujarat. Its primary importance stems from the **Jetalsar Railway Junction**, which connects several major routes across the Saurashtra region.
        </p>

        <h2>Key Town Facts</h2>
        <div class="fact-box">
            <p><strong>Location:</strong> Rajkot District, Gujarat, India.</p>
            <p><strong>Primary Role:</strong> Major Railway Junction (JTL).</p>
            <p><strong>Significance:</strong> Acts as a gateway connecting parts of Kathiawar with other regions.</p>
        </div>

        <h2>Railway Connections & Routes</h2>
        <ul class="feature-list">
            <li>
                <strong>Jetalsar - Rajkot Line</strong> (Route)<br>
                Description: The key connection to the largest city and commercial center in the region.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Jetalsar - Veraval Line</strong> (Route)<br>
                Description: Connects the junction to major pilgrimage centers like Somnath.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Jetalsar - Porbandar Line</strong> (Route)<br>
                Description: Links the junction to the coastal city of Porbandar.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>

